1903//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1904void File_MpegTs::Read_Buffer_Continue()
1905{
1906 if (!IsSub)
1907 {
1908 if (Config->ParseSpeed>=1.0)
1909 Config->State_Set(((float)Buffer_TotalBytes)/File_Size);
1910 else if (Buffer_TotalBytes>MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin+MpegTs_JumpTo_End)
1911 Config->State_Set((float)0.99); //Nearly the end
1912 else
1913 Config->State_Set(((float)Buffer_TotalBytes)/(MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin+MpegTs_JumpTo_End));
1914 }
1915
1916 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1917 if (Complete_Stream && pid<0x2000 && Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Kind==complete_stream::stream::pes && Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Parser && ((File_MpegPs*)Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Parser)->Demux_StreamIsBeingParsed_type!=(int8u)-1)
1918 {
1919 Open_Buffer_Continue(Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Parser, Buffer, 0, false);
1920 PES_Parse_Finish();
1921 }
1922 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1923}
1924
1925//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1926void File_MpegTs::Read_Buffer_AfterParsing()
1927{
1928 if (Complete_Stream==NULL)
1929 return; //No synchronization yet
1930
1931 if (!Status[IsFilled])
1932 {
1933 //Test if parsing of headers is OK
1934 if ((Complete_Stream->Streams_NotParsedCount==0 && (Complete_Stream->NoPatPmt || (Complete_Stream->transport_stream_id_IsValid && Complete_Stream->Transport_Streams[Complete_Stream->transport_stream_id].Programs_NotParsedCount==0)))
1935 || (Buffer_TotalBytes-Buffer_TotalBytes_FirstSynched>=MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin && Config->ParseSpeed<0.8)
1936 || File_Offset+Buffer_Size==File_Size)
1937 {
1938 //Test if PAT/PMT are missing (ofen in .trp files)
1939 if (!Complete_Stream->transport_stream_id_IsValid
1940 && !Complete_Stream->NoPatPmt)
1941 {
1942 //Activating all streams as PES
1943 SetAllToPES();
1944 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format_Profile, "No PAT/PMT");
1945 Buffer_TotalBytes=0;
1946 Buffer_TotalBytes_LastSynched=(int64u)-1;
1947 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
1948 GoTo(0);
1949 return;
1950 }
1951
1952 //Filling
1953 for (std::set<int16u>::iterator StreamID=Complete_Stream->PES_PIDs.begin(); StreamID!=Complete_Stream->PES_PIDs.end(); ++StreamID)
1954 {
1955 if (Complete_Stream->Streams[*StreamID]->Parser)
1956 {
1957 Fill(Complete_Stream->Streams[*StreamID]->Parser);
1958
1959 Complete_Stream->Streams[*StreamID]->Parser->Status[IsUpdated]=false;
1960 Complete_Stream->Streams[*StreamID]->IsUpdated_Info=true;
1961 }
1962
1963 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Complete_Stream->Streams[*StreamID]->program_numbers.size(); Pos++)
1964 Complete_Stream->Transport_Streams[Complete_Stream->transport_stream_id].Programs[Complete_Stream->Streams[*StreamID]->program_numbers[Pos]].Update_Needed_IsRegistered=true;
1965 }
1966 Complete_Stream->Streams_NotParsedCount=0;
1967 Fill();
1968
1969 //Deactivating
1970 if (Config->File_StopSubStreamAfterFilled_Get())
1971 for (std::set<int16u>::iterator StreamID=Complete_Stream->PES_PIDs.begin(); StreamID!=Complete_Stream->PES_PIDs.end(); ++StreamID)
1972 {
1973 Complete_Stream->Streams[*StreamID]->Searching_Payload_Start_Set(false);
1974 Complete_Stream->Streams[*StreamID]->Searching_Payload_Continue_Set(false);
1975 }
1976
1977 //Status
1978 Status[IsUpdated]=true;
1979 Status[User_19]=true;
1980
1981 //
1982 if (!(Buffer_TotalBytes-Buffer_TotalBytes_FirstSynched>=MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin && Config->ParseSpeed<0.8))
1983 {
1984 MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset-Buffer_TotalBytes_FirstSynched;
1985 MpegTs_JumpTo_End=MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin;
1986
1987 //Avoid too short duration of the end. e.g. with quick pass, MpegTs_JumpTo_End may have content only for 2 frames which is not enough for catching an I-frame at the end of the file. Forcing to 2 seconds
1988 if (Config->ParseSpeed < 0.5)
1989 {
1990 complete_stream::streams::iterator It_End=Complete_Stream->Streams.end();
1991 for (complete_stream::streams::iterator It=Complete_Stream->Streams.begin(); It!=It_End; ++It)
1992 {
1993 complete_stream::stream* &Stream=*It;
1994
1995 if (Stream && Stream->Kind==complete_stream::stream::pes && Stream->TimeStamp_Start!=(int64u)-1)
1996 {
1997 int64u Duration=Stream->TimeStamp_End-Stream->TimeStamp_Start;
1998 if (Duration<27000000*2) // 2 seconds
1999 {
2000 int64u Ratio=(27000000*2)/Duration;
2001 MpegTs_JumpTo_End*=Ratio;
2002 break; //Using the first PES found
2003 }
2004 }
2005 }
2006 }
2007
2008 if (MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin+MpegTs_JumpTo_End>=File_Size)
2009 {
2010 if (MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin+MpegTs_JumpTo_End>File_Size)
2011 {
2012 MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin=File_Size;
2013 MpegTs_JumpTo_End=0;
2014 }
2015 else
2016 MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin=File_Size-MpegTs_JumpTo_End;
2017 }
2018 }
2019
2020 //Jumping
2021 if (Config->ParseSpeed<1.0 && Config->File_IsSeekable_Get()
2022 #if MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
2023 && (!Config->File_IgnoreSequenceFileSize_Get() || Config->File_Names_Pos!=Config->File_Names.size()) // TODO: temporary disabling theses options for MPEG-TS (see above), because it does not work as expected
2024 #endif //MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
2025 && MpegTs_ScanUpTo == (int64u)-1
2026 && File_Offset+Buffer_Size<File_Size-MpegTs_JumpTo_End && MpegTs_JumpTo_End)
2027 {
2028 #if !defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PCR_YES) && !defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PESTIMESTAMP_YES)
2029 GoToFromEnd(47); //TODO: Should be changed later (when Finalize stuff will be split)
2030 #else //!defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PCR_YES) && !defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PESTIMESTAMP_YES)
2031 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_EIA608_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_EIA708_YES)
2032 if (File_Offset+Buffer_Size<File_Size/2-MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin && File_Size/2+MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin<File_Size-MpegTs_JumpTo_End && ((Config->File_DtvccTransport_Stream_IsPresent && !Config->File_DtvccTransport_Descriptor_IsPresent)
2033 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_EIA608_YES)
2034 || Config->File_Scte20_IsPresent
2035 #endif //defined(MEDIAINFO_EIA608_YES)
2036 ))
2037 {
2038 MpegTs_ScanUpTo=File_Size/2+MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin;
2039 GoTo(File_Size/2-MpegTs_JumpTo_Begin);
2040 }
2041 else
2042 #endif //defined(MEDIAINFO_EIA608_YES) || defined(MEDIAINFO_EIA708_YES)
2043 GoToFromEnd(MpegTs_JumpTo_End);
2044 Searching_TimeStamp_Start=false;
2045 #endif //!defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PCR_YES) && !defined(MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PESTIMESTAMP_YES)
2046 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
2047 }
2048 }
2049 }
2050
2051 if (MpegTs_ScanUpTo != (int64u)-1 && File_Offset+Buffer_Size>=MpegTs_ScanUpTo)
2052 {
2053 MpegTs_ScanUpTo = (int64u)-1;
2054 GoToFromEnd(MpegTs_JumpTo_End);
2055 Open_Buffer_Unsynch();
2056 }
2057}

2325 Program_Numbers+=Ztring::ToZtring_From_CC2(Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->program_numbers[Pos])+__T('/');
2326 if (!Program_Numbers.empty())

2340 }

2393//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2394void File_MpegTs::Header_Parse_AdaptationField()
2395{
2396 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
2397 if (Trace_Activated)
2398 {
2399 int64u Element_Pos_Save=Element_Offset;
2400 Element_Begin1("adaptation_field");
2401 int8u adaptation_field_length;
2402 Get_B1 (adaptation_field_length, "adaptation_field_length");
2403 if (adaptation_field_length>188-4-1) //TS size - header - adaptation_field_length
2404 {
2405 adaptation_field_length=188-4-1;
2406 Skip_XX(188-4-1, "stuffing_bytes");
2407 }
2408 else if (adaptation_field_length>0)
2409 {
2410 bool discontinuity_indicator, PCR_flag, OPCR_flag, splicing_point_flag, transport_private_data_flag, adaptation_field_extension_flag;
2411 BS_Begin();
2412 Get_SB ( discontinuity_indicator, "discontinuity_indicator");
2413 Skip_SB( "random_access_indicator");
2414 Skip_SB( "elementary_stream_priority_indicator");
2415 Get_SB ( PCR_flag, "PCR_flag");
2416 Get_SB ( OPCR_flag, "OPCR_flag");
2417 Get_SB ( splicing_point_flag, "splicing_point_flag");
2418 Get_SB ( transport_private_data_flag, "transport_private_data_flag");
2419 Get_SB ( adaptation_field_extension_flag, "adaptation_field_extension_flag");
2420 BS_End();
2421 if (PCR_flag)
2422 {
2423 #ifdef MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PCR_YES
2424 BS_Begin();
2425 int64u program_clock_reference_base;
2426 int16u program_clock_reference_extension;
2427 Get_S8 (33, program_clock_reference_base, "program_clock_reference_base"); Param_Info_From_Milliseconds(program_clock_reference_base/90);
2428 Data_Info_From_Milliseconds(program_clock_reference_base/90);
2429 Skip_S1( 6, "reserved");
2430 Get_S2 ( 9, program_clock_reference_extension, "program_clock_reference_extension");
2431 int64u program_clock_reference=program_clock_reference_base*300+program_clock_reference_extension;
2432 Param_Info1(program_clock_reference);
2433 BS_End();
2434 if (Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Searching_TimeStamp_End
2435 #ifdef MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PESTIMESTAMP_YES
2436 && (!Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Searching_ParserTimeStamp_End
2437 || Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->IsPCR) //If PCR, we always want it.
2438 #endif //MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PESTIMESTAMP_YES
2439 )
2440 {
2441 Header_Parse_Events_Duration(program_clock_reference);
2442 if (program_clock_reference!=Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End) //Some PCRs are buggy (low precision), using the first stream offset in the case of duplicate PCR value
2443 {
2444 if (Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End_Offset!=(int64u)-1)
2445 {
2446 if (program_clock_reference+0x12c00000000LL<Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End)
2447 program_clock_reference+=0x25800000000LL; //33 bits and *300
2448 if (!discontinuity_indicator && program_clock_reference>Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End && program_clock_reference<Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End+10*27000000) //Not before, not after 10 seconds, else there is a problem
2449 {
2450 float64 Duration_InstantaneousBitRate_Min=(float64)(program_clock_reference-Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End-(Config_VbrDetection_Delta?0:810));
2451 float64 Duration_InstantaneousBitRate_Max=(float64)(program_clock_reference-Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End+(Config_VbrDetection_Delta?0:810));
2452 float64 Bytes_InstantaneousBitRate=(float64)(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset-Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End_Offset);
2453 float64 TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Min=Bytes_InstantaneousBitRate*8/Duration_InstantaneousBitRate_Max*27000000*(1-Config_VbrDetection_Delta);
2454 float64 TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Raw=Bytes_InstantaneousBitRate*8/Duration_InstantaneousBitRate_Min*27000000;
2455 float64 TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Max=Bytes_InstantaneousBitRate*8/Duration_InstantaneousBitRate_Min*27000000*(1+Config_VbrDetection_Delta);
2456 if (Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Min)
2457 {
2458 if (TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Max<Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Min || TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Min>Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Max)
2459 {
2460 Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_BitRateMode_IsVbr++;
2461 #if MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
2462 if (Config_VbrDetection_GiveUp && Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_BitRateMode_IsVbr>=Config_VbrDetection_Occurences)
2463 Config->ParseSpeed=0;
2464 #endif // MEDIAINFO_ADVANCED
2465 }
2466 else
2467 Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_BitRateMode_IsCbr++;
2468 }
2469 float64 Duration_Min=(float64)(program_clock_reference-Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End-1);
2470 float64 Duration_Raw=(float64)(program_clock_reference-Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End);
2471 float64 Duration_Max=(float64)(program_clock_reference-Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End+1);
2472 float64 Bytes=(float64)(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset-Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_End_Offset);
2473 float64 TimeStamp_Min=Bytes*8/Duration_Max*27000000*(1-Config_VbrDetection_Delta);
2474 float64 TimeStamp_Raw=Bytes*8/Duration_Raw*27000000;
2475 float64 TimeStamp_Max=Bytes*8/Duration_Min*27000000*(1+Config_VbrDetection_Delta);
2476 Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Min=TimeStamp_Min;
2477 Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Raw=TimeStamp_Raw;
2478 Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->TimeStamp_InstantaneousBitRate_Current_Max=TimeStamp_Max;

2850//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2851void File_MpegTs::Data_Parse()
2852{
2853 //Counting
2854 Frame_Count++;
2855
2856 //TSP specific
2857 if (TSP_Size)
2858 Element_Size-=TSP_Size;
2859
2860 #if MEDIAINFO_DUPLICATE
2861 if (Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->ShouldDuplicate)
2862 File__Duplicate_Write();
2863 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DUPLICATE
2864
2865 //Parsing
2866 if (!Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Searching_Payload_Start
2867 && !Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Searching_Payload_Continue
2868 #ifdef MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PESTIMESTAMP_YES
2869 && !Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Searching_ParserTimeStamp_Start
2870 && !Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Searching_ParserTimeStamp_End
2871 #endif //MEDIAINFO_MPEGTS_PESTIMESTAMP_YES
2872 )
2873 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "data");
2874 else
2875 switch (Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Kind)
2876 {
2877 case complete_stream::stream::pes : PES(); break;
2878 case complete_stream::stream::psi : PSI(); break;
2879 default: ;
2880 }
2881
2882 //TSP specific
2883 if (TSP_Size)
2884 {
2885 Element_Size+=TSP_Size;
2886 switch(TSP_Size)
2887 {
2888 case 16: Skip_B16( "TSP"); break; //TSP supplement
2889 default: Skip_XX(TSP_Size, "TSP");
2890 }
2891 }
2892}

2912 {
2913 Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->IsRegistered=true;
2914 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->program_numbers.size(); Pos++)

2917 Complete_Stream->Transport_Streams[Complete_Stream->transport_stream_id].Programs[Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->program_numbers[Pos]].Update_Needed_IsRegistered=true;
2918
2919 Complete_Stream->Transport_Streams[Complete_Stream->transport_stream_id].Programs[Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->program_numbers[Pos]].IsRegistered=true;
2920 }
2921
2922 Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->IsUpdated_IsRegistered=true;
2923 Complete_Stream->PES_PIDs.insert(pid);
2924
2925 Status[IsUpdated]=true;
2926 Status[User_19]=true;
2927 }
2928
2929 //Case of encrypted streams
2930 if (transport_scrambling_control)
2931 {
2932 if (!Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Searching_Payload_Continue)
2933 Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Searching_Payload_Continue_Set(true); //In order to count the packets
2934
2935 if (Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Scrambled_Count>16)
2936 {
2937 //Don't need anymore
2938 Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Searching_Payload_Start_Set(false);
2939 Complete_Stream->Streams[pid]->Searching_Payload_Continue_Set(false);

3363 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE

3365 Trace_Activated=false;
3366 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
3367 Element_Begin1("SCTE 128 coherency test");
3368 bool IsOk=true;
3369 while (Element_Offset+2<=End)
3370 {
3371 int8u tag, length;
3372 Get_B1 (tag, "tag");
3373 Get_B1 (length, "length");
3374 if (Element_Offset+length>End || (tag==0xDF && length<4))

3386 }

3388 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE

3390 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE

3395 {
3396 Element_Begin0();
3397 int8u tag, length;
3398 Get_B1 (tag, "tag"); Param_Info1(Scte128_tag(tag)); Element_Name(Scte128_tag(tag));
3399 Get_B1 (length, "length");
3400 if (tag==0xDF && length>=4)
3401 {
3402 int32u format_identifier;
3403 Get_C4 (format_identifier, "format identifier");
3404 switch (format_identifier)
3405 {
3406 case 0x45425030 : //EBP0
3407 {
3408 int64u End2=Element_Offset+length-4;
3409 Element_Info1("CableLabs - Encoder Boundary Point");
